The paper deals with the application of deep neural networks to predict the behavior of a dynamical system modeled by partial differential equations. This falls under the domain of computational science and engineering (cs.CE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of neural networks for prediction tasks is a common application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the comparison of recurrent and convolutional neural networks, which are both popular architectures in the field of neural networks and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the generalization capability of the networks, which is a common topic in the field of neural networks and optimization (cs.NE).
